<i>That EG6 may be faster</i>
<i>than Takumi's Eight-Six...</i>

00:03:42.420 --> 00:03:44.890
Who's driving it?

00:04:09.380 --> 00:04:11.740
Thank you very much!

00:04:13.720 --> 00:04:16.350
I was really furious!

00:04:16.350 --> 00:04:21.720
So, he was braking while
cornering... at high speed?

00:04:21.720 --> 00:04:25.560
I don't think I've ever seen anything like it.

00:04:25.560 --> 00:04:27.160
Really?

00:04:27.160 --> 00:04:30.270
Everybody does that!

00:04:30.270 --> 00:04:34.600
I step on the brake while
cornering all the time.

00:04:39.070 --> 00:04:40.940
Uh-oh, I'm going too fast...

00:04:40.940 --> 00:04:43.180
I'm scared... step, step...

00:04:43.180 --> 00:04:45.880
We're not talking about a beginner...

00:04:45.880 --> 00:04:52.390
This EG6 cleared those downhill
turns at an incredible speed.

00:04:52.390 --> 00:04:54.620
EG6?

00:04:54.620 --> 00:04:57.690
It's a Honda Civic!

00:04:57.690 --> 00:05:00.700
Why don't they just call it a Civic, then?

00:05:00.700 --> 00:05:02.960
The Civic is very popular among street racers,

00:05:02.960 --> 00:05:05.400
even though it's an FF.

00:05:05.400 --> 00:05:09.800
It's a non-turbo 1.6 liter like your Eight-Six,

00:05:09.800 --> 00:05:15.980
but its VTEC engine has tons of power.

00:05:15.980 --> 00:05:19.810
It has been a rival of the Levin
and the Trueno for years.

00:05:19.810 --> 00:05:24.690
As an Eight-Six driver,
you should know about the Civic.

00:05:24.690 --> 00:05:26.990
As a Levin driver myself...

00:05:26.990 --> 00:05:29.980
