00:05:31.930 --> 00:05:36.400
Anyway, I just can't believe
it went in at that speed

00:05:36.400 --> 00:05:37.930
and then braked.

00:05:37.930 --> 00:05:42.770
Well, that technique is called left foot braking.

00:05:42.770 --> 00:05:44.370
Left foot braking?

00:05:44.370 --> 00:05:49.240
You usually don't use
this technique with an FR,

00:05:49.240 --> 00:05:51.850
but you brake with the left foot

00:05:51.850 --> 00:05:55.420
to stabilize the car at
an extremely high speed.

00:05:55.420 --> 00:05:57.890
With an FF like an EG6,

00:05:57.890 --> 00:06:00.590
you need your right foot on
the gas pedal continuously

00:06:00.590 --> 00:06:03.020
to avoid understeering,

00:06:03.020 --> 00:06:05.690
so you brake with your left foot

00:06:05.690 --> 00:06:09.500
to take the weight off the rear
tires and turn more sharply.

00:06:09.500 --> 00:06:14.400
He must be a highly experienced
FF driver to use that technique.

00:06:14.400 --> 00:06:17.670
I'm sure he's fast.

00:06:17.670 --> 00:06:21.810
He was pretty fast... That punk...

00:06:21.810 --> 00:06:24.880
I only avoided crashing
because I'd just practiced

00:06:24.880 --> 00:06:27.820
spinning with the emergency brake.

00:06:27.820 --> 00:06:31.220
Otherwise, my S13 would've
been in the shop again!

00:06:31.220 --> 00:06:35.750
I'm gonna make that EG6 pay!

